==English==

===Adjective===
'''curve'''

# (''obsolete'') Bent without angles; crooked; curved.
#:''a curve line''
#:''a curve surface''

====Translations====
''See'' '''[[crooked]]''' ''and'' '''[[curved]]'''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A gentle [[bend]], such as in a road.
# A figure containing no [[straight]] portions and no [[angle]]s.
# (''geometry'') A [[one-dimensional]] figure of [[non-zero]] length.
# (''analytic geometry'')  A [[continuous map]] from a one-dimensional [[space]] to a multidimensional space, or its [[graph]].
# (''algebra'') An [[algebraic curve]]; a [[polynomial]] [[relation]] of the planar coordinates.
# (''topology'') A one-dimensional [[continuum]].
# (''informal, usually in plural'' '''curves''') The attractive shape of a woman's body.

